The South African Students Congress is going ahead with a national shutdown of tertiary institutions on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Students Congress is going ahead with plans for a total shutdown on Monday. Sasco is calling for the clearing and end to historic debt, among other things. WATCH: SA Union of Students briefs media The shutdown will follow hot on the heels of the Wits student protests in Braamfontein last week. eNCA’s Tshegohaco Moagi shares more details in the video above